---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/UI/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/UI/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy | Paschalis Gkikas"
  description="Privacy policy and personal data protection of the medical practice. Information on data processing, GDPR, and patient rights."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 bg-slate-50 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">Privacy Policy & Data Protection</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">Last Update: 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-sm border border-slate-200">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700">
          
          <p>Our website is fully committed to protecting the personal data of its visitors and patients. We will not disclose patient information to third parties unless it is absolutely necessary to provide you with a service, under the terms of this Policy and with your consent or where we are required by law (e.g., based on medical confidentiality or a court order).</p>
          
          <p>Our website handles personal data in accordance with the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and relevant Greek laws. The data we collect is always relevant and appropriate for the fulfillment of our medical obligations.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Medical Confidentiality & Record Keeping</h2>
          <p>Psychiatrist Paschalis Gkikas (+30 211 8500016) informs you regarding the processing of your personal data:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>According to <strong>Article 14 of Law 3418/2005 (Code of Medical Ethics)</strong>, keeping a medical record is mandatory (Full name, age, address, reason for visit, diagnosis, examinations). The record is kept for <strong>10 years</strong> after your last visit.</li>
            <li>The doctor maintains strictly necessary security measures to safeguard your personal data.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
          <p>As a patient, you have the following rights:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> To request a copy of your medical file.</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> To correct inaccurate information.</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion ("Right to be Forgotten"):</strong> To request the deletion of your data (taking into account the doctor's 10-year legal obligation).</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> To request restriction of processing.</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> To have your data sent to a third party (e.g., another doctor of your choice).</li>
          </ul>
          <p>In any case, the doctor is bound by the Code of Medical Ethics to ensure medical confidentiality and protect patient information to the absolute degree.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Data Collection Methods</h2>
          <p>We collect personal data through contact forms and telephone communication <strong>only</strong> if you voluntarily choose to do so to arrange an appointment. This data is processed exclusively by the doctor and authorized office staff, using strict encryption measures.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Cookies Policy</h2>
          <p>Cookies are small pieces of information stored on your browser, allowing us to provide a smooth experience on our website (e.g., collecting anonymous traffic statistics, Google Analytics).</p>
          <p><strong>They do not cause damage</strong> to your computers. You can change your browser settings at any time to refuse the storage of cookies.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Data Deletion & Access</h2>
          <p>The doctor retains personal data in accordance with the law. Anyone wishing to access, correct, or delete (to the extent legally permitted) may send a written request to our <a href="mailto:contact@drgkikas.com">email</a> or via the Contact page.</p>

        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
